The paper deals with the manipulation of a lock using operations that can be represented by unitary matrices, which is a topic in quantum computing. The concept of quantum automatic complexity is also introduced, which is a measure of the complexity of a word in terms of the number of unitary matrices required to manipulate it. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), or cs.QI (Quantum Physics). However, since the paper focuses on quantum computing and quantum automatic complexity, cs.QI is the most likely category, followed by cs.ET and cs.CC. The other categories are less likely but still possible, as they are related to the theoretical aspects of computer science that are relevant to the paper.
